info.description:
This API retrieves policy data from legacy systems (Auto & Fire) as well as Policy Center - Business Lines (Auto & Fire) and Personal Lines (Auto Private Passenger). The ouput can be specified in either PCMM or AMM format.

Input Parameter Guidance

The agreementAccessKey, agreementIndexId, and policySearchKey are mutually exclusive - only one of the three is required. The existence of the 'filters' query parameter specifies that detail data is to be returned, and if left off, only summary data will returned. Additionally, the physicalObjNumber & physicalObjectIdentifier are mutually exclusive--these parameters represent the car number. **Note** For AMM format, add the following parameter &dataFormat=AMM. If this parameter is not passed, the default for a detail call is PCMM. *
Sample URL for auto policy detail data with asOfDate and filters specified. Response will be in PCMM format.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=3521497200&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&asOfDate=2019-02-12 *
Sample URL for PLM (Policy Center - Personal Lines) auto policy detail with filters specified and POID (Physical Object Identifier). Response will be in PCMM format.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=3520058002&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&physicalObjectIdentifier=55401 *
Sample URL for auto policy detail data with no asOfDate and filters specified. Response will be in AMM format.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=3521497200&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&dataFormat=AMM *
Sample URL for fire policy detail data with asOfDate and filters specified. Response will be in PCMM format.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=016093K8200KF6&asOfDate=2019-02-12&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT *
Sample URL for auto policy summary data. **Note, summary responses are currently on in AMM, so no dataFormat parameter is needed.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=3521497200&asOfDate=2018-01-01 *
Sample URL for the retrieval of latest term. **Note, this only applies for retrieve detail calls on PMR and FMR policies.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?productLine=A&agreementAccessKey=4330000345&asOfDate=2019-05-19&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&retrieveLatestTerm=Y *
Sample URL for the policy detail data with asOfDate, sourceSystemCode and filters specified.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?productLine=A&agreementAccessKey=4330000345&asOfDate=2019-05-19&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&sourceSystemCode=1 *
Sample URL for auto policy summary data when sourceSystemCode is provided. **Note, summary responses are currently on in AMM, so no dataFormat parameter is needed.
* /PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=3521497200&asOfDate=2018-01-01&sourceSystemCode=24
**Note** The HTTP parameter **esb_restPath** must be provided for the service to function. In test, an environment suffix is required, and in production, only the base value is required>> 'B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2' To access the Policy Retrieval API in test, use one of the following Domain VIPs with the corresponding esb_restPath HTTP header: | Domain VIP | Environment | HTTP Parm: esb_restPath | --- | --- | --- | | sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | TEST1 | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/TEST1 | | sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | SYSTF | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/SYSTF | | sfesb-dev.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | SYSTD | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/SYSTD | | sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | TEST3 | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/TEST3 | | sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | TEST5 | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/TEST5 | | sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | SYSTE | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/SYSTE | | sfesb-qc.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | Performance | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2 | | sfesb-prep.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | Pre-Prod | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2 | | sfesb.opr.statefarm.org/B2E/REST | Production | B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2 | * **Full Auto URL example** * http://sfesb-sys.opr.test.statefarm.org/B2E/REST/PolicyRetrieval-Web_v2/services/rest/IRetrievePolicyService/policies?agreementAccessKey=131C002680&filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT&dataFormat=AMM * **AMM Maven Dependency** * <dependency> <groupId>sf.psdata.amm</groupId> <artifactId>agreement-message-usage</artifactId> <version>**2.0.1-RC-55**</version> </dependency> * **PCMM Schema** * **PCMM Schema** * **Error Scenarios** * **DVL Error Handling** ## Contact Manager - Jody Gaydos(jpfz) Product Owner - Michelle Clemons(jial) **Email:** DL-ET-DataVirtualization-WG9197
info.title: Data Virtualization - Policy Data Retrieval

get.description: The example response/model shown below contains a representation of both PCMM & AMM, with the PCMM being first, followed by AMM. Within the PolicyResponseObject, there is an InsurancePolicy object, which represents the PCMM, and a Policy object which represents AMM. Please see the input parameter documentation below.

parameters.name: agreementAccessKey
parameters.description: Agreement Access Key (Required, if not providing a policySearchKey or agreementIndexId)

parameters.name: agreementIndexId
parameters.description: Agreement Index Id (Required, if not providing a agreementAccessKey or policySearchKey)

parameters.name: asOfDate
parameters.description: As of Date, allows for narrowing by effective date

parameters.name: dataFormat
parameters.description: Data Format Switch. PCMM or AMM format switch. Usage: If no parameter is provided, output defaults to PCMM, otherwire pass dataFormat=AMM if desired.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: The filters parameter specifies coverages in a comma separated list, and must pass at least one value. If this parameter is passed, detail policy data will be provided, otherwise it will be summary.Usage: filters=POLICY,RISK,COVERAGE,PHYOBJCT

parameters.name: physicalObjNumber
parameters.description: Physical Object Number [vehicle number]. This only applies to Legacy PMR Auto policies. If this is not provided, a list of all vehicles for the given policy will be returned.

parameters.name: physicalObjectIdentifier
parameters.description: Physical Object Identifier [vehicle number]. This only applies to Personal Lines (PLM) Auto policies. If this is not provided, a list of all vehicles for the given policy will be returned in PCMM format.

parameters.name: policySearchKey
parameters.description: Policy Search Key (Required, if not providing agreementIndexId or agreementAccessKey)

parameters.name: policyTermPublicIdentifier
parameters.description: Policy Term Public Identifier (Only applies to PLM policies). If this is provided, all other parameters are ignored.

parameters.name: retrieveLatestTerm
parameters.description: Retrieve latest term indicator. An indicator that when set to 'Y', will result in the latest term being retrieved when a term for the effective date(asOfDate) is not found.

parameters.name: sourceSystemCode
parameters.description: Source System Code Switch and the possible values are 1,15,24,25,26. Usage: If sourceSystemCode is provided, we eliminate the AI call to retrieve policy information
